cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a robotic pick-and-place system.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the system uses image classification for object recognition.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the system uses a category-agnostic affordance prediction algorithm and cross-domain image classification framework.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the system uses pre-trained models for recognition and grasping.
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is less likely but still possible as the system involves coordination between the robot and its environment.
